Uses of Package
org.oucs.oxpoints.exceptions

Packages that use org.oucs.oxpoints.exceptions
org.oucs.oxpoints.entities OxPointsEntitys are java representations of objects from the OxPoints ontology. 
org.oucs.oxpoints.entities.pool OxPointsEntityPools are collections of OxPointsEntitys. 
org.oucs.oxpoints.entities.time While OxPointsEntitys are representation of OxPoints objects at a specific point in time, OxPointsTimeBasedEntity represent an OxPoints object over its lifespan. 
org.oucs.oxpoints.entities.transformation Contains Annotations and abstract classes that are used for transforming OxPointsEntityPools and OxPointsEntitys. 
org.oucs.oxpoints.exceptions Contains various exceptions that are used in the OxPoints system. 
org.oucs.oxpoints.helperscripts Groups helper scripts than can be run from the command line. 
org.oucs.oxpoints.model Contains the classes implementing the data model. 
org.oucs.oxpoints.model.query Contains an interface to write simple predefined queries that can be transformed on the fly into various output formats. 
org.oucs.oxpoints.model.query.defined Contains all predefined queries. 
org.oucs.oxpoints.reflection   
org.oucs.oxpoints.sample   
org.oucs.oxpoints.test.classes Contains various unit tests to test the functionality of the OxPoints system. 
org.oucs.oxpoints.test.classes.randommodel Tests that generate random triples to test some functionality of the OxPoints system. 
org.oucs.oxpoints.test.performance   
org.oucs.oxpoints.timedim.index Contains an interface and implementations of an index for time bound named graphs.

Classes in org.oucs.oxpoints.exceptions used by org.oucs.oxpoints.entities.pool

          Is thrown when it is suspected that the data in OxPoints is corrupted.
EntityClassNotFoundException
          Is thrown when the corresponding OxPointsEntity class for an ontology type could not be determined.
EntityDoesNotExistException
          Is thrown when an OxPointsEntity is accessed that does not exist in the model.
EntityPoolAmbiguousConfigurationException
          Is thrown if the OxPointsEntityPoolConfiguration can be used for the creation of an OxPointsEntityPool, but if it is ambiguous in some way.
EntityPoolInvalidConfigurationException
          Is thrown if an OxPointsEntityPoolConfiguration is invalid.
ResourceDoesNotExistException
          Is thrown when an RDF resource is accessed that does not exist.
